Here's a PlantUML sequence diagram representing the control flow of the Knowledge Graph Visualization application based on the provided repository summary:

```plantuml
@startuml Crazy0416_KnowledgeGraph

actor User
participant "UI" as UI
participant "GraphController" as GC
participant "SearchEngine" as SE
participant "Sigma.js" as Sigma
participant "Elasticsearch" as ES
participant "CayleyGraph" as CG

User -> UI: Interact with interface
UI -> GC: Request graph visualization
GC -> Sigma: Initialize graph
Sigma -> GC: Return graph instance
GC -> UI: Display graph

User -> UI: Enter search keywords
UI -> SE: Send search request
SE -> ES: Query data
ES -> SE: Return relevant RDF data
SE -> GC: Process search results
GC -> Sigma: Update graph visualization
Sigma -> UI: Render updated graph

User -> UI: Request path between nodes
UI -> GC: Calculate path
GC -> GC: Apply A* algorithm
GC -> Sigma: Highlight path
Sigma -> UI: Display highlighted path

User -> UI: Zoom/pan graph
UI -> Sigma: Apply layout changes
Sigma -> GC: Update graph layout
GC -> Sigma: Apply Noverlap algorithm
Sigma -> UI: Render adjusted layout

User -> UI: Interact with graph element
UI -> GC: Handle interaction
GC -> CG: Query additional data if needed
CG -> GC: Return queried data
GC -> Sigma: Update graph based on interaction
Sigma -> UI: Render interaction results

@enduml
```